00071 /**
00072  * \addtogroup LSDynaFileIO
00073  * \brief LS-Dyna file IO.
00074  *
00075  * \description
00076  * 
00077  *    FCLib does not provide a writer for LS-Dyna files. 
00078  *
00079  *    The file IO for d3plot binary files is based on the documentation
00080  *    in "LS-DYNA Database Binary Output Files" January 1994 Revised May 2002.
00081  *    HOWEVER, there were a lot of places where the documentation differed
00082  *    from actual LS-DYNA files. The ultimate resource should be the code
00083  *    in lsdynaio.c, as we are reasonable sure of its correctness. We
00084  *    have also tried to document these differences in comments within the
00085  *    code, and also below.
00086  *
00087  *    This reader is not completely general, and will not work on LS-DYNA d3plot
00088  *    files with SPH nodes, thick shell elements, fluid materials or CFD
00089  *    values.
00090  *
00091  *    Documentation differences:
00092  *    - In Control Data section and the State Data section, we have encountered
00093  *      datasets where the number of global variables (NGLBV) is 1, although 
00094  *      NGLBV is usually > 7. We have no idea which of the 7 normal global vars
00095  *      it is.
00096  *    - In Control Data section and the State Data section, NGLBV = <b>7</b> +
00097  *      6*(NUMMAT8 + ...) + NUMRW. (7 instead of 6).
00098  *    - In the Geometry Data section, the 2 node beam element connectivities 
00099  *      come before the 4 node shell element connectivities, not after.
00100  *    - In the User Material, Node and Element Identification Numbers section, 
00101  *      the total section length is increased by 6 +
00102  *      <b>3</b>*(NUMMAT8+NUMMAT4+NUMMAT2+NUMMATT). (The 3 was missing.)
00103  *    - In the User Material, Node and Element Identification Numbers section,
00104  *      some dataset seem to be padded and total section length is less than
00105  *      NARBS.
00106  *    - In the State Data section, the documentation implies that the
00107  *      temperature nodal variable comes first. It actually comes second. The
00108  *      order of nodal variables is: displacement, temperature, velocity, 
00109  *      acceleration.
00110  *
00111  *    Misc notes:
00112  *    - We never read the number of rigid wall global vars and instead
00113  *      calculate them using the formula for the total number of global vars.
00114  *    - The element data is written as all data for an element, then all
00115  *      data for the next element (= striped).
00116  *    - Note that while elements are in order based on element type, the
00117  *      parts/meshes are not in any particular order. \ref
00118  *      _fc_calcLSDynaElemChunks() creates "chunk" information that maps
00119  *      from partIDs back into the element data arrays. 
00120  *
00121  * \todo Combine stress tensor scalars into 1 variable.
00122  */

00124 /**
00125  * \ingroup LSDynaFileIO
00126  * \brief Helper function to change Endianness.
00127  *
00128  * \description 
00129  *
00130  *    Will only handle 4 or 8 bytes.
00131  */
00132 static void _fc_swapEndian(void* Addr, size_t size) {
00133   unsigned char* word = (unsigned char*)Addr;
00134   unsigned char temp[4];
00135   switch(size) {
00136   case 4:
00137     temp[0] = word[0];
00138     temp[1] = word[1];
00139     word[0] = word[3];
00140     word[1] = word[2];
00141     word[2] = temp[1];
00142     word[3] = temp[0];
00143     break;
00144   case 8:
00145     temp[0] = word[0];
00146     temp[1] = word[1];
00147     temp[2] = word[2];
00148     temp[3] = word[3];
00149     word[0] = word[7];
00150     word[1] = word[6];
00151     word[2] = word[5];
00152     word[3] = word[4];
00153     word[4] = temp[3];
00154     word[5] = temp[2];
00155     word[6] = temp[1];
00156     word[7] = temp[0];
00157   }
00158 }

00196 /**
00197  * \ingroup LSDynaFileIO
00198  * \brief Helper function to do endianSwap while reading from file.
00199  *
00200  * \description 
00201  *
00202  *    This function wraps fread and performs the requested read with the
00203  *    following additional functionalities:
00204  *      - checks to see if we've reach the end of the current file
00205  *        and opens the next file if so.
00206  *      - reorders bits if the reading platform has a different Endianness
00207  *        than the writing platform did.
00208  *
00209  *    The last argument is optional (can pass NULL) and only applies
00210  *    if an error condition is returned. If the flag is 1, then the routine
00211  *    could not find a next file (this is how we tell we are done in
00212  *    the main read routine).
00213  *   
00214  * \modifications
00215  *    - 8/5/2005 WSD Added automatically opening the next file.
00216  */
00217 static FC_ReturnCode _fc_fread_endianSwap(
00218    void* ptr,    /**< output - pointer to already allocated buffer to read 
00219                     into */
00220    size_t size,  /**< input - the size of each object */
00221    size_t nmemb, /**< input - the number of objects */ 
00222    FILE** file,  /**< input/output - the current file to read from */
00223    char* basename, /**< input - the base file name */
00224    int* fileNum,   /**< input/output - pointer to the current file number */
00225    int doEndianSwap, /**< input - flag for whether to flip bits */
00226    int* noNextFile   /**< output - flag, 1 means error condition is 
00227                         because there is no next file */
00228 ) {
00229   size_t count, i;
00230   char filename[1024] = ""; // root names are limited to 75 char
00231   char test[size];
00232 
00233   // default return
00234   if (noNextFile)
00235     *noNextFile = 0;
00236 
00237   // read
00238   count = fread(ptr, size, nmemb, *file);
00239 
00240   // Take first entry & swap endian so can test for 'end of file' word
00241   if (count > 0) {
00242     memcpy(test, ptr, size);
00243     if (doEndianSwap)
00244       _fc_swapEndian(&test, size);
00245   }
00246 
00247   // If an error or see 'end of file' word, try opening another file
00248   if (count != nmemb || _fc_getDoubleFromBuffer(test, size, 0) == -999999) {
00249     fclose(*file);
00250     // check all the way up to 999, 'cause they are allowed to skip #'s
00251     while(*fileNum < 999) {
00252       (*fileNum)++;
00253       if (*fileNum < 100)
00254      sprintf(filename, "%s%02d", basename, *fileNum);
00255       else if (*fileNum < 1000)
00256      sprintf(filename, "%s%03d", basename, *fileNum);
00257       fc_printfLogMessage("Attempting to open next file '%s'", filename);
00258       *file = fopen(filename, "r");
00259       if (*file != NULL)
00260      break;
00261     }
00262     // If fail to find file, return special code.
00263     if (*file == NULL) { 
00264       if (noNextFile)
00265         *noNextFile = 1;
00266       // no error message on purpose since not always an error
00267       return FC_ERROR;
00268     }
00269     // Reread
00270     count = fread(ptr, size, nmemb, *file);
00271     if (count != nmemb) {
00272       fc_printfErrorMessage("Read failed. Expected count of %d, got %d", 
00273                             (int)nmemb, (int)count); 
00274       return FC_FILE_IO_ERROR;
00275     }
00276   }
00277 
00278   // swap bits
00279   if (doEndianSwap) {
00280     for (i = 0; i < nmemb; i++)
00281       _fc_swapEndian((char*)ptr + i*size, size);
00282   }
00283 
00284   return FC_SUCCESS;
00285 }

00287 /**
00288  * \ingroup LSDynaFileIO
00289  * \brief Helper to discover how elements are assigned to parts (chunked).
00290  *
00291  * \description
00292  *
00293  *    Connectivity information is stored per element, but the order of elements
00294  *    is kinda random. This routine uses the partID stored with each element to
00295  *    create "chunk" offsets and "chunk" lengths to make grabbing element data
00296  *    later for a specific part easier. (Chunk = contiguous group of elements
00297  *    from the same part; a part may have 1 or more chunks).
00298  *
00299  *    The results are ordered by partID, not by element type. So even though
00300  *    the first element is a solid, it might be in part 3; and a shell element
00301  *    might be in the first part.
00302  *   
00303  * \modifications
00304  *    - 9/2006 created WSD.
00305  */
00306 static FC_ReturnCode _fc_calcLSDynaElemChunks(
00307   int numTotalMesh,
00308   int numTotalVert,
00309   FC_ElementType elemType,
00310   int numMesh,
00311   int numElem,
00312   FC_ElementType *elemTypes,
00313   int* numVerts,
00314   int* numElems,
00315   int** vertIDs,
00316   int* numElemChunks,
00317   int** startElemPerChunk,
00318   int** numElemPerChunk,
00319   int wordlen,
00320   FILE** file,
00321   char* filename,
00322   int* fileNum,
00323   int doEndianSwap
00324 )
00325 {
00326   // FIX bars don't follow numVertPerElem+1 convention
00327   // I think the below code is correct, but needs to be checked
00328   FC_ReturnCode rc;
00329   int i, j, k, m;
00330   int prevMeshID, count, meshCount, *vertLU;
00331   void* temp, *temp2;
00332   int numVertPerElem, numPlus;
00333   
00334   // setup
00335   numVertPerElem = fc_getElementTypeNumVertex(elemType);
00336   numPlus = numVertPerElem + 1;
00337   if (elemType == FC_ET_LINE)
00338     numPlus = 6; // atypical case, discard values at indices 2-4
00339  
00340   // Read the conns plus part IDs
00341   int* global_conns_plus = (int*)malloc(numPlus*numElem*sizeof(int));
00342   if (!global_conns_plus) {
00343     fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_MEMORY_ERROR));
00344     return FC_MEMORY_ERROR;
00345   }
00346   if (wordlen == 4) {
00347     rc = _fc_fread_endianSwap(global_conns_plus, wordlen, 
00348                     numPlus*numElem, file,
00349                     filename, fileNum, doEndianSwap, NULL);
00350     if (rc != FC_SUCCESS) {
00351       fc_printfErrorMessage("Failed to read element conns");
00352       return rc;
00353     }
00354   }
00355   else {
00356     long long *temp_conns_plus = (long long*)malloc(numPlus*
00357                              numElem*sizeof(long long));
00358     rc = _fc_fread_endianSwap(temp_conns_plus, wordlen, 
00359                     numPlus*numElem, file,
00360                     filename, fileNum, doEndianSwap, NULL);
00361     if (rc != FC_SUCCESS) {
00362       fc_printfErrorMessage("Failed to read element conns");
00363       return rc;
00364     }
00365     for (i = 0; i < numPlus*numElem; i++)
00366       global_conns_plus[i] = temp_conns_plus[i];
00367     free(temp_conns_plus);
00368   }
00369   
00370   // Cannot assume that all elements for a part will be in 1 continguous block.
00371   // so, walk global_conns_plus once to determine blocks for each mesh 
00372   prevMeshID = -1;
00373   for (i = 0; i < numElem; i++) {
00374     // Note: MeshID = PartID - 1
00375     int meshID = global_conns_plus[i*numPlus + numPlus-1] - 1;
00376     if (meshID != prevMeshID) {
00377       elemTypes[meshID] = elemType;
00378       temp = realloc(numElemPerChunk[meshID], 
00379                (1+numElemChunks[meshID])*sizeof(int));
00380       temp2 = realloc(startElemPerChunk[meshID], 
00381                (1+numElemChunks[meshID])*sizeof(int));
00382       if (!temp || !temp2) {
00383      fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_MEMORY_ERROR));
00384      return FC_MEMORY_ERROR;
00385       }
00386       numElemPerChunk[meshID] = temp;
00387       startElemPerChunk[meshID] = temp2;
00388       numElemPerChunk[meshID][numElemChunks[meshID]] = 1;
00389       startElemPerChunk[meshID][numElemChunks[meshID]] = i;
00390       numElemChunks[meshID]++;
00391       prevMeshID = meshID;
00392     }
00393     else
00394       numElemPerChunk[meshID][numElemChunks[meshID]-1]++;
00395   }
00396 
00397   // this data structure is used anew in each loop below
00398   vertLU = (int*)malloc(numTotalVert*sizeof(int)); // global -> local
00399   if (!vertLU) {
00400     fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_MEMORY_ERROR));
00401     return FC_MEMORY_ERROR;
00402   }
00403 
00404   // creating global -> local, and local to global vert LUTs
00405   // Also filling in numElems & numVerts (per part)
00406   meshCount = 0;
00407   for (i = 0; i < numTotalMesh; i++) { // loop over meshes
00408     // skip meshes that are not of the current element type
00409     if (elemTypes[i] != elemType)
00410       continue;
00411     meshCount++;
00412     // examine conns &  calc numElems[i], calc numVerts[i]
00413     // assign new ID numbers, collect globalIDs
00414     // initialize global -> local LUT
00415     for (j = 0; j < numTotalVert; j++) 
00416       vertLU[j] = -1;
00417     numElems[i] = 0;
00418     for (j = 0; j < numElemChunks[i]; j++) { // loop over chunks
00419       int current_offset = numPlus*startElemPerChunk[i][j];
00420       numElems[i] += numElemPerChunk[i][j];
00421       for (k = 0; k < numElemPerChunk[i][j]; k++) { // l. elems in chunks
00422      for (m = 0; m < numVertPerElem; m++) {
00423        // global IDs start with 1, so have to subtract 1 off
00424        vertLU[global_conns_plus[current_offset+m]-1] = 0;
00425      }
00426      current_offset += numPlus;
00427       }
00428     }
00429     numVerts[i] = 0;
00430     for (j = 0; j < numTotalVert; j++) {
00431       if (vertLU[j] > -1) {
00432         vertLU[j] = numVerts[i]; // new ID
00433         numVerts[i]++;
00434       }
00435     }
00436     vertIDs[i] = (int*)malloc(numVerts[i]*sizeof(int));
00437     if (!vertIDs[i]) {
00438       fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_MEMORY_ERROR));
00439       return FC_MEMORY_ERROR;
00440     }
00441     count = 0;
00442     for (j = 0; j < numTotalVert; j++) {
00443       if (vertLU[j] > -1) {
00444         vertIDs[i][count] = j;
00445         count++;
00446       }
00447     } 
00448   }
00449   free(global_conns_plus);
00450   free(vertLU);
00451 
00452   // consistency check
00453   if (meshCount != numMesh) {
00454     fc_printfErrorMessage("didn't process the expected number of meshes");
00455     return FC_ERROR;
00456   }
00457 
00458   return FC_SUCCESS;
00459 }

01076       varSlot->assoc = FC_AT_ELEMENT;

01079       varSlot->header.committed = 1;

01081       varSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.data_offset = ftell(file);
01082       varSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.isStriped = 0;

01086     // get mat IDs and use in mesh names
01087     if (doMatNums) {

01091       // check NMMAT
01092       numMat =_fc_getIntFromBuffer(wordBuf, wordlen, 5);

01103      return FC_MEMORY_ERROR;
01104       }
01105       rc = _fc_fread_endianSwap(tempWordBuf, wordlen, numMat, &file, filename,

01107       for (i = 0; i < numTotalMesh; i++) {
01108      if (FC_HANDLE_EQUIV(meshes[i], FC_NULL_MESH))
01109        continue;
01110      meshSlot = _fc_getMeshSlot(meshes[i]);

01112      sprintf(tempName, "Material_ID_%d", meshSlot->fileInfo.id);

01116

01118       fseek(file, 2*numMat*wordlen, SEEK_CUR);
01119     }
01120 
01121     // NOTE: For some reason, some datasets seem to be padded ... skip padding
01122     if (temp_count != numArbWord)
01123       fseek(file, (numArbWord - temp_count)*wordlen, SEEK_CUR);
01124   }
01125 
01126   //--- Read the names file, if it exists, & rename meshes
01127   rc = _fc_readNamesFile(filename, &block_names, &nodeset_names, &sideset_names);
01128   if (rc != FC_SUCCESS)
01129     return rc;
01130   if (block_names.numBlob > 0) {
01131     // rename meshes
01132     for (i = 0; i < numTotalMesh; i++) {
01133       int key;
01134       if (FC_HANDLE_EQUIV(meshes[i], FC_NULL_MESH))
01135      continue;
01136       meshSlot = _fc_getMeshSlot(meshes[i]);
01137       if (!strncmp(meshSlot->header.name, "part", 4)) 
01138      key = atoi(&meshSlot->header.name[5]);
01139       else
01140      key = atoi(&meshSlot->header.name[12]);
01141       if (fc_isBlobInSortedBlobArray(&block_names, &key, fc_intCompare,
01142                          (void**)&blob)) {
01143      _fc_setSlotHeaderName(&meshSlot->header, blob->string);
01144       }
01145       // else - keep current name
01146     }
01147   }
01148   _fc_freeNamesFileNames(&block_names, &nodeset_names, &sideset_names);
01149 
01150   //--- Read state data section (might be in multiple files, but assume
01151   //    first state is in first file)
01152 
01153   // (Assume all of a single state will be in the same file).
01154 
01155   // NOTE: because the State Data will span multiple files, it's difficult
01156   // to figure out the total number of states a priori, so we'll just have
01157   // to grow arrays of things instead of a priori allocation.
01158 
01159   // NOTE: There is a special case not documented in LS-DYNA documentation,
01160   // where numTotalGlbVar = 1. In that case, there are no per material global 
01161   // vars and no per rigid wall global vars.
01162   // (p.s. some day might want to have a flag other than numTotalGlbVar)
01163   if (numTotalGlbVar == 1) {
01164     numGlbVar = numTotalGlbVar;
01165     numPerMatGlbVar = 0;
01166     numRW = 0;
01167   }

01173   }
01174 
01175   // Total number of vars we need to turn into seqvars
01176   // Store vars as we make them, turn into seqvars at very end

01186     return FC_MEMORY_ERROR;
01187   }
01188   for (i = 0; i < numSeqVar; i++) {
01189     vars[i] = (FC_Variable*)malloc(sizeof(FC_Variable));
01190     if (vars[i] == NULL) {
01191       fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_MEMORY_ERROR));
01192       return FC_MEMORY_ERROR;
01193     }
01194   }
01195 
01196   numStep = 0;
01197   maxStep = 1;
01198   time_coords = (void*)malloc(wordlen);
01199   if (!time_coords) {
01200     fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_MEMORY_ERROR));
01201     return FC_MEMORY_ERROR;
01202   }
01203   while (1) {
01204     int noNextFile;
01205 
01206     // read time coord value,
01207     rc = _fc_fread_endianSwap(&wordBuf, wordlen, 1, &file, filename, &fileNum,
01208                                doEndianSwap,&noNextFile);
01209     if (rc != FC_SUCCESS) {
01210       if (noNextFile)
01211         break; // no more files, we're done! (the file was closed)
01212       else {
01213         fc_printfErrorMessage("Failed to read time coord");
01214         fclose(file);
01215         return FC_FILE_IO_ERROR; // error => exit function
01216       }
01217     }
01218 
01219     // expand arrays if needed
01220     if (numStep >= maxStep) {
01221       void* temp_p;
01222       FC_Variable* temp_vars;

01230       for (i = 0; i < numSeqVar; i++) {
01231         temp_vars = (FC_Variable*)realloc(vars[i],maxStep*sizeof(FC_Variable));
01232         if (temp_vars == NULL) {
01233           fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_MEMORY_ERROR));
01234           return FC_MEMORY_ERROR;
01235         }
01236         vars[i] = temp_vars;
01237       }
01238     }
01239 
01240     // Assign time coord value
01241     if (wordlen == 4) 
01242       ((float*)time_coords)[numStep] = _fc_getDoubleFromBuffer(wordBuf, wordlen,0);

01244       ((double*)time_coords)[numStep] = _fc_getDoubleFromBuffer(wordBuf,wordlen,0);

01246     // init seqVarID
01247     seqVarID = 0;
01248 
01249     // True Global variables
01250     for (i = 0 ; i < numGlbVar; i++) {
01251       rc = fc_createGlobalVariable(*dataset, globalVarNames[i],
01252                                    &vars[seqVarID][numStep]);
01253       if (rc != FC_SUCCESS) {
01254         fc_printfErrorMessage("failed to create global var '%s'",

01256           return rc;
01257       }
01258       varSlot = _fc_getVarSlot(vars[seqVarID][numStep]);
01259       varSlot->numDataPoint = 1;
01260       varSlot->numComponent = globalVarNumComps[i];
01261       varSlot->assoc = FC_AT_WHOLE_DATASET;
01262       if (globalVarNumComps[i] == 1)
01263         varSlot->mathtype = FC_MT_SCALAR;
01264       else
01265         varSlot->mathtype = FC_MT_VECTOR;
01266       varSlot->datatype = datatype;
01267       varSlot->header.committed = 1;
01268       varSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.dataFileNum = fileNum;
01269       varSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.data_offset = ftell(file);

01289           varSlot->numDataPoint = 1;
01290           varSlot->numComponent = perMatVarComps[i];
01291           varSlot->assoc = FC_AT_WHOLE_MESH;
01292           if (perMatVarComps[i] == 1)
01293             varSlot->mathtype = FC_MT_SCALAR;
01294           else
01295             varSlot->mathtype = FC_MT_VECTOR;
01296           varSlot->datatype = datatype;
01297           varSlot->header.committed = 1;
01298           varSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.dataFileNum = fileNum;
01299           varSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.data_offset = ftell(file);
01300           varSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.doDispl = 0;

01350       }
01351       else if (doVelVar && i == doDisplVar + doTempVar) {
01352         seqVarName = velVarName;
01353      mathType = FC_MT_VECTOR;
01354      temp_numDim = numDim;
01355       }
01356       else if (doAccelVar && i == doDisplVar + doTempVar + doVelVar) {
01357         seqVarName = accelVarName;
01358      mathType = FC_MT_VECTOR;
01359      temp_numDim = numDim;
01360       }
01361       for (j = 0; j < numTotalMesh; j++) {
01362      if (FC_HANDLE_EQUIV(meshes[j], FC_NULL_MESH))

01365                                &vars[seqVarID][numStep]);

01373         varSlot->numDataPoint = meshSlot->numVertex;
01374      varSlot->numComponent = temp_numDim;
01375         varSlot->assoc = FC_AT_VERTEX;

01409                                 "mesh #%d", seqVarName, i);
01410           return rc;
01411         }
01412         varSlot = _fc_getVarSlot(vars[seqVarID][numStep]);
01413         meshSlot = _fc_getMeshSlot(meshes[i]);
01414         varSlot->numDataPoint = meshSlot->numElement;
01415         varSlot->numComponent = 1;
01416         varSlot->assoc = FC_AT_ELEMENT;
01417         varSlot->mathtype = FC_MT_SCALAR;
01418         varSlot->datatype = datatype;

01421         varSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.data_offset = ftell(file);

01443                                &vars[seqVarID][numStep]);

01445           fc_printfErrorMessage("failed to create scalar var '%s' on "
01446                                 "mesh #%d", seqVarName, i);
01447           return rc;
01448         }
01449         varSlot = _fc_getVarSlot(vars[seqVarID][numStep]);
01450         meshSlot = _fc_getMeshSlot(meshes[i]);
01451         varSlot->numDataPoint = meshSlot->numElement;
01452         varSlot->numComponent = 1;
01453         varSlot->assoc = FC_AT_ELEMENT;
01454         varSlot->mathtype = FC_MT_SCALAR;
01455         varSlot->datatype = datatype;
01456         varSlot->header.committed = 1;
01457         varSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.dataFileNum = fileNum;
01458         varSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.data_offset = ftell(file);
01459         varSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.isStriped = numElemVar2;
01460         varSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.stripeID = j;

01489         varSlot = _fc_getVarSlot(vars[seqVarID][numStep]);

01520         meshSlot = _fc_getMeshSlot(meshes[i]);

01559     fc_printfErrorMessage("Failed to create sequence");
01560     return rc;
01561   }
01562   rc = fc_setSequenceCoordsPtr(sequence, numStep, datatype, time_coords);

01565 
01566   //--- Create sequence variables - convert the created vars to seq variables
01567   for (i = 0; i < numSeqVar; i++) {

01578   //--- All done

01706 /**
01707  * \ingroup  LSDynaFileIO
01708  * \brief  Read data from LS-DYNA file into a mesh
01709  *
01710  * \description
01711  *  
01712  *    Assuming that the given mesh had already been setup, then read the 
01713  *    mesh element connectivities.
01714  *
01715  * \modifications
01716  *   - 7/18/2005 WSD.
01717  */
01718 FC_ReturnCode _fc_readLSDynaMeshElemConns(
01719   FC_Mesh mesh     /**< input - mesh to be read into */
01720 ) {
01721   FC_ReturnCode rc;
01722   int i, j, k;
01723   _FC_MeshSlot* meshSlot;
01724   _FC_DsSlot* dsSlot;
01725   FILE* file;
01726   int* conns;
01727   void* temp_conns;
01728   int numVertPerElem, numPlus;
01729   int* vertLU, numVert;
01730   char filename[1024]; // root names are limited to 75 char 
01731   int fileNum;
01732   int meshID, numElem;
01733   long offset;
01734 
01735   // check input
01736   meshSlot = _fc_getMeshSlot(mesh);
01737   if (!meshSlot || !meshSlot->header.name) {
01738     fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_INPUT_ERROR));
01739     return FC_INPUT_ERROR;
01740   }
01741   
01742   // log message
01743   fc_printfLogMessage("Reading conns for  mesh '%s'", meshSlot->header.name);
01744 
01745   // setup
01746   meshID = meshSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.meshID;
01747   dsSlot = _fc_getDsSlot(meshSlot->ds);
01748   numVertPerElem = fc_getElementTypeNumVertex(meshSlot->elemType);
01749   numPlus = numVertPerElem + 1;
01750   if (meshSlot->elemType == FC_ET_LINE)
01751     numPlus = 6;
01752   if (meshSlot->elemType == FC_ET_HEX)
01753     offset = dsSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.conns8_offset;
01754   else if (meshSlot->elemType == FC_ET_QUAD)
01755     offset = dsSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.conns4_offset;
01756   else if (meshSlot->elemType == FC_ET_LINE)
01757     offset = dsSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.conns2_offset;
01758  
01759   // open the file
01760   fileNum = dsSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.coordsFileNum;
01761   if (fileNum  == 0)
01762     strcpy(filename, dsSlot->baseFile);
01763   else if (fileNum < 100)
01764     sprintf(filename, "%s%02d", dsSlot->baseFile, fileNum);
01765   else
01766     sprintf(filename, "%s%d", dsSlot->baseFile, fileNum);
01767   file = fopen(filename, "r");
01768   if (file == NULL) {
01769     fc_printfErrorMessage("could't open file '%s'", filename);
01770     return FC_FILE_IO_ERROR;
01771   }
01772 
01773   // setup - make room for the conns
01774   conns = malloc(meshSlot->numElement*numVertPerElem*sizeof(int));
01775   if (!conns) {
01776       fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_MEMORY_ERROR));
01777       return FC_MEMORY_ERROR;
01778   }
01779 
01780   // Read conns in blocks (but will be in global verts + has partID)
01781   // copy into conns into new array w/o partID
01782   numElem = 0;
01783   for (i = 0; i < dsSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.numElemChunks[meshID]; i++) {
01784     int numElemPerChunk = dsSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.numElemPerChunk[meshID][i];
01785     temp_conns = malloc(numElemPerChunk*numPlus*
01786                dsSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.wordlen);
01787     if (!temp_conns) {
01788       fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_MEMORY_ERROR));
01789       return FC_MEMORY_ERROR;
01790     }  
01791     fseek(file, offset + numPlus*dsSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.wordlen*
01792        dsSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.startElemPerChunk[meshID][i], SEEK_SET);
01793     rc = _fc_fread_endianSwap(temp_conns, dsSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.wordlen, 
01794                     numElemPerChunk*numPlus, &file, 
01795                     dsSlot->baseFile, &fileNum, 
01796                     dsSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.doEndianSwap, NULL);
01797     if (rc != FC_SUCCESS) {
01798       fc_printfErrorMessage("Failed to read mesh conns");
01799       free(temp_conns);
01800       return rc;
01801     }
01802 
01803     if (dsSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.wordlen == 4) {
01804       int* cast_conns = (int*)temp_conns;
01805       for (j = 0; j < numElemPerChunk; j++) { 
01806      for (k = 0; k < numVertPerElem; k++) 
01807        conns[numElem*numVertPerElem+k] = cast_conns[j*numPlus+k];
01808      numElem++;
01809       }
01810     }
01811     else {
01812       long long* cast_conns = (long long*)temp_conns;
01813       for (j = 0; j < numElemPerChunk; j++) { 
01814      for (k = 0; k < numVertPerElem; k++)
01815        conns[numElem*numVertPerElem+k] = cast_conns[j*numPlus+k];
01816      numElem++;
01817       }
01818     }
01819     free(temp_conns);
01820   }
01821   if (numElem != meshSlot->numElement) {
01822     printf("****** oh no, mismatch of numElement ******!\n");
01823     fflush(NULL);
01824   }
01825 
01826   // Close file
01827   fclose(file);
01828 
01829   // Convert to local verts
01830   // Make vertLU
01831   vertLU = (int*)malloc(dsSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.numTotalVert*sizeof(int));
01832   if (!vertLU) {
01833     fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_MEMORY_ERROR));
01834     return FC_MEMORY_ERROR;
01835   }
01836   for (i = 0; i < dsSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.numTotalVert; i++)
01837     vertLU[i] = -1;
01838   for (i = 0; i < meshSlot->numElement; i++) 
01839     for (j = 0; j < numVertPerElem; j++)
01840       vertLU[conns[i*numVertPerElem+j]-1] = 0;
01841   numVert = 0;
01842   for (i = 0; i <dsSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.numTotalVert; i++) {
01843     if (vertLU[i] > -1) {
01844       vertLU[i] = numVert;
01845       numVert++;
01846     }
01847   }
01848   if (numVert != meshSlot->numVertex) {
01849     printf("****** oh no, mismatch of numVertex ******!\n");
01850     fflush(NULL);
01851   }
01852   for (i = 0; i < numVertPerElem*meshSlot->numElement; i++)
01853     conns[i] = vertLU[conns[i]-1];
01854   free(vertLU);
01855 
01856   // done
01857   meshSlot->elemToVertConns = conns;
01858   return FC_SUCCESS;
01859 }

02113      for (j = 0; j < numElemPerChunk; j++)

02116       }

02119      return FC_ERROR;
02120       }
02121       numElem += numElemPerChunk;
02122       free(temp_data);

02126   // fifth case - what if not one of the other 4 cases
02127   else {

02129     return FC_ERROR;
02130   }

02176 /**
02177  * \ingroup  LSDynaFileIO
02178  * \brief  Ask if any vertices are shared.
02179  *
02180  * \description 
02181  *
02182  *    Because LS-DYNA has a single global list of vertices and FCLib has local
02183  *    lists of vertices per mesh, it is possible for a single global vertex to
02184  *    show up in multiple meshes.
02185  *
02186  *    Returns true (>1), false (0), or -1 if the dataset is not an
02187  *    LS-DYNA Dataset.
02188  *
02189  * \modifications  
02190  *   - 2/3/2006 WSD, created.
02191  */
02192 int _fc_hasSharedLSDynaVertices(
02193   FC_Dataset dataset /**< input - the dataset */
02194 ) {
02195   FC_ReturnCode rc;
02196   int i,j;
02197   _FC_DsSlot* dsSlot;
02198   int* counts, numShare;
02199   int numMesh, numVert;
02200   FC_Mesh* meshes;
02201   _FC_MeshSlot *meshSlot;
02202 
02203   // check input
02204   dsSlot = _fc_getDsSlot(dataset);
02205   if (dsSlot == NULL) {
02206     fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_INPUT_ERROR));
02207     return FC_INPUT_ERROR;
02208   }
02209 
02210   // setup
02211   rc = fc_getMeshes(dataset, &numMesh, &meshes);
02212   if (rc != FC_SUCCESS)
02213     return rc;
02214 
02215   // Early return - no meshes, no shared global verts
02216   if (numMesh < 1)
02217     return 0;
02218 
02219   // collect counts
02220   counts = (int*)calloc(dsSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.numTotalVert, sizeof(int));
02221   if (!counts) {
02222     fc_printfErrorMessage("%s", fc_getReturnCodeText(FC_MEMORY_ERROR));
02223     return FC_MEMORY_ERROR;
02224   }
02225   for (i = 0; i < numMesh; i++) {
02226     int meshID;
02227     meshSlot = _fc_getMeshSlot(meshes[i]);
02228     meshID = meshSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.meshID;
02229     if (meshID < 0 || meshID >= dsSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.numMesh)
02230       continue; // this isn't an lsdyna mesh
02231     fc_getMeshNumVertex(meshes[i], &numVert);
02232     if (rc != FC_SUCCESS)
02233       return rc;
02234     for (j = 0; j < numVert; j++) 
02235       counts[dsSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.vertIDs[meshID][j]]++;
02236   }
02237   free(meshes);
02238 
02239   // look at counts
02240   numShare = 0;
02241   for (i = 0; i < dsSlot->fileInfo.dynaInfo.numTotalVert; i++) {
02242     if (counts[i] > 1)
02243       numShare++;
02244     else if (counts[i] < 1)
02245       printf("***** ieeee ***\n");
02246   }
02247   return numShare;
